<item>
            <title>[LU-19470] Incorrect file size after truncate following POSIX fallocate on Lustre ZFS</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19470</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using &lt;tt&gt;&apos;fallocate --posix&apos;&lt;/tt&gt; on a Lustre filesystem with ZFS backend&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. The standard &lt;tt&gt;&apos;fallocate&apos;&lt;/tt&gt; is attempted first&lt;br/&gt;
2. Due to ZFS not supporting standard &lt;tt&gt;&apos;fallocate&apos;&lt;/tt&gt;, it falls back to POSIX writes for space pre-allocation&lt;br/&gt;
3. A subsequent truncate operation results in an unexpected file size&lt;br/&gt;
4. The issue can be resolved by using &lt;tt&gt;&apos;lfs migrate&apos;&lt;/tt&gt; on the affected file, but not LFSCK,&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-bash&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;# Setup test environment
&lt;/span&gt;MOUNT_POINT=/mnt/lustre
TEST_DIR=${MOUNT_POINT}/test_dir
FILE=$TEST_DIR/temp_test_file
mkdir -p ${TEST_DIR}
rm -f &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$FILE&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;# Configure progressive file layout (1MB with 1 stripe, remainder with 2 stripes)
&lt;/span&gt;lfs setstripe -E 1M -c 1 -E -1 -c 2 $TEST_DIR

&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;# Create test file
&lt;/span&gt;dd &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;=/dev/urandom of=&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$FILE&lt;/span&gt; bs=1M count=1
echo &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&quot;MD5 original: $(md5sum &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$FILE&lt;/span&gt; | awk &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&apos;{print &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$1&lt;/span&gt;}&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;# this returns 0
&lt;/span&gt;fallocate -l 2M --posix &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$FILE&lt;/span&gt;
echo $?

&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;# metadata is already &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&quot;corrupted&quot;&lt;/span&gt; so truncate will behave incorrectly
&lt;/span&gt;truncate -s 1M &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$FILE&lt;/span&gt;
echo &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&quot;MD5 after truncate: $(md5sum &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$FILE&lt;/span&gt; | awk &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&apos;{print &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$1&lt;/span&gt;}&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;# expect to see 1M but we get 2M
&lt;/span&gt;du -b &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$FILE&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;# Attempt repair with LFSCK (will not fix fallocate corruption)
&lt;/span&gt;sudo lctl lfsck_start -A -r -t all -C -c -o -d &amp;gt; /dev/null
sudo lctl lfsck_query -w &amp;gt; /dev/null
echo &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&quot;MD5 after lfsck: $(md5sum &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$FILE&lt;/span&gt; | awk &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&apos;{print &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$1&lt;/span&gt;}&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;# Repair with lfs migrate (effective solution)
&lt;/span&gt;sudo lfs migrate &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$FILE&lt;/span&gt;
echo &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&quot;MD5 after migrate: $(md5sum &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$FILE&lt;/span&gt; | awk &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&apos;{print &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;$1&lt;/span&gt;}&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tested using Lustre 2.15.6&lt;/p&gt;</description>
